00:21:06.959 --> 00:21:12.719
succeed in building tools to fill the missing gaps that will enable us to achieve that multi-engine

00:21:13.439 --> 00:21:18.560
data stack. And the hope is that we make it accessible, you know, through all the programming

00:21:18.560 --> 00:21:25.040
languages that we use, including R and Python, and we work to continue to work together to build

00:21:25.040 --> 00:21:32.000
shared infrastructure that we can all use. So 41 slides. Thank you for listening,

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:37.119
and I will probably yield my slot to somebody else next year because I've spoken enough at

00:21:37.119 --> 00:21:43.920
this conference, but in any case I look forward to seeing you again in the future. Thank you.

